<item>
            <title>[SOLR-10444] SQL interface does not use client cache</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-10444</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the new SQL interface does not use the Solr client cache. This causes new instances of CloudSolrClient to be created with each query. These instances are being closed, but this is still not good because the connection to Zk needs to be established on each request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a fairly easy fix so I&apos;d like to get this in for Solr 6.5.1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
